Unable to hear, speak, or wield a sword, Prince Bojji doesn’t seem like a typical heir to the throne—and his kingdom agrees. But his fateful encounter with Kage, a shadow on the ground, gives him his first true friend. The two set off on a grand adventure and, together, form a bond that can overcome any obstacle...even being king.
(Source: Funimation)

Satoru Fujinuma is a 29 year old manga artist struggling to make a name for himself following his debut. But, that was not the only thing in his life that Satoru was feeling frustrated about… He has a unique supernatural ability of being forced to prevent deaths and catastrophes by being sent back in time before the incident occurred, repeating time until the accident is prevented. One day, he gets involved in an accident that has him framed as a murderer. Desperate to save the victim, he sends himself back in time only to find himself as a grade-schooler one month before fellow classmate Kayo Hinazuki went missing. Satoru now embarks on a new quest: to save Kayo and solve the mystery behind her disappearance.
Takane-san, Kimi no Koto Sukirashii yo

"I heard that Takamine-san likes you."
The head of the school discipline committee, Kengo Mashima, heard a rumor from an unknown source...... It turned out that the source was none other than Takamine-san herself, who wanted Mashima-kun to show more interest in her! But the overly serious Mashima-kun didn't get the hint: ......
"Saki Takamine, I heard you have a crush on me?"
"Why are you asking me for? ......!"
Actually, Mashima-kun liked Takamine-san, too. The first time you see these two, you'll be writhing in frustration at their innocent denseness!
(Source: Gagaga Bunko, translated)
Konbini Goutou kara Tasuketa Jimi Tenin ga, Onaji Class no Ubude Kawaii Gal datta

"Do you want to stay at my place… for tonight?"

Kuramine Riku, a second-year high school boy, is feeling down after getting dumped by his childhood friend. He enters a convenience store and happens to save the store clerk who was being attacked. The clerk is Ayana Hoshimiya, the most popular and beautiful gal in school. The incident causes Hoshimiya to tell him about a stalker, and the two of them decides to live together so he could protect her...?

(Source: Fantasia Bunko, translated)
